<BLOCK1><TI>ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS APPEAL</BOLD> by the Attorney General of Ontario, the Defendant / Appellant, from the Order of the Honourable Mr. Justice Stinson, dated January 4, 2017, dismissing the Appellant's motion to strike the Statement of Claim and dismiss the underlying action because it is barred by the expiry of a limitation period was heard on October 30 and 31, 2018 at the Court of Appeal, 130 Queen Street West, Toronto, Ontario, and judgment was reserved until this day.</P>
<P><BOLD>ON READING</BOLD> the Appeal Book and Compendium; the Factum, and Book of Authorities of the Appellant; and the Factum and Book of Authorities of the Respondents,</P>
<P><BOLD>AND ON HEARING</BOLD> the submissions of counsel for the Appellant and counsel for the Respondents,
<P1><BOLD>1. THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the appeal is dismissed.</P1>
<P1><BOLD>2. THIS COURT FURTHER ORDERS</BOLD> that costs are payable by the Appellant in the amount of $5,000, inclusive of disbursements and HST.</P1>
<P1><BOLD>3. THIS ORDER</BOLD> bears interest at the rate of 3 per cent per year commencing on April 18, 2019.</P1></P>
<P>&ellip35; Registrar</P></BLOCK1>
