<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS MOTION</BOLD> made by the Attorney General of Ontario, the defendant, to strike the Statement of Claim and dismiss this action pursuant to Rule 21 because it is barred by the expiry of a limitation period was heard this day at 393 University Avenue, Toronto, Ontario.</P>
<P><BOLD>ON READING</BOLD> the motion record, factum, and book of authorities of the. defendant, and the responding factum and book of authorities of the plaintiffs, and on hearing the submissions of counsel for the plaintiffs and the defendant,
<P1><BOLD>1. THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the defendant's motion to strike the claim because it is barred by the expiry of the applicable limitation period is dismissed.</P1>
<P1><BOLD>2. THIS COURT FURTHER ORDERS</BOLD> that there be no Order as to costs.</P1></P>
